resources.string: The ODM version check has failed! This means the os is currently using a version of the proprietary binaries, which your Android is not build for. This may will work without further problems, but could also harm your device.\n Please consider upgrading your them as soon as possible. Commonly you could just flash the oem partition(s) with them - but for further reference please visit a guide for your device (you may press the button below).\n When you are the maintainer of this rom you should think about overriding the respective property.
Your system is running an unsupported version of the software binaries. Tap here to learn more!
